The paper discusses compressed sensing techniques for the acquisition of continuous-time spectrally sparse signals, which falls under the signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT) categories. The paper also investigates the relationship between two specific compressed sensing techniques, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper proposes a new acquisition system for block-sparse signals, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper discusses the sensitivity of the systems to sparse signal model assumptions, which could fall under the statistics (cs.ST) category. However, since the paper does not explicitly mention statistical methods, cs.ST is less likely than the other categories mentioned.
